  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 20 for SLE 15)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 4.12.14-150_58 fixes several issues.\n\nThe following security issues were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2021-3444: Fixed an issue with the bpf verifier which did not properly handle mod32 destination register truncation when the source register was known to be 0 leading to out of bounds read  (bsc#1184171).\n- CVE-2021-28688: Fixed an issue introduced by XSA-365 (bsc##1182294, bsc#1183646).\n- CVE-2021-26930: Fixed an improper error handling in blkback's grant mapping (XSA-365 bsc#1182294).\n- CVE-2021-26931: Fixed an issue where Linux  kernel was treating grant mapping errors as bugs (XSA-362 bsc#1183022).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
